children.value: In this scenario we will cover a single Farm with a single Farm Harvest. We will be building a PGA Record based off the Events below. The Master Data for these events can be found above in the Master Data section.
There are attributes required by SIMP that are not part of the GDST guidance. Here are recommendations on how these attributes could be recorded in EPCIS in order to meet SIMP requirements.
- This can be recorded as an additional attribute either in the Party or Location master data. The recommended CBV attribute is "urn:gdst:iftp".
In order to not repeat the master data used with each example, I would like to provide the master data used in the examples below.
In order to fill out a SIMP report for a Aquaculture scenario we will need the following KDEs:
- Pulled from the Country of Origin in the ILMD data of the Fishing Event
- Pulled from the Event Time of the Offload Event.
- Pulled from the Master Data of the Vessel / Party. In this example we will pull it from the Master Data of the Vessel Owning Party.
- Pulled from the Master Data for Owning Party of the BizLocation of event with the disposition of "entering_commerce".
- Pulled from the Master Data for the BizLocation of event with the disposition of "entering_commerce".
- Pulled from the Master Data for the BizLocation of the event with the disposition of "entering_commerce".
- Pulled from the Master Data for the BizLocation of the event with the disposition of "entering_commerce".
- Pulled from the Master Data for the BizLocation of the event with the disposition of "entering_commerce".
- Pulled from the Net Weight recorded for the Product in the Offload Event
- Pulled from the Product Form of the Master Data of the Offloaded product.that occurs.
This event covers how the Feed is created and the ingredients that go into making the feed.
This event covers the creation of the Broodstock that will be used for stocking a pond at an aquaculture facility.
This event covers the harvesting of a product from a pond at an aquaculture event. This is a transformation event where the input is the Broodstock and Feed and the output is the harvested product.
<!-- INPUT: Vegetarian Feed + Antlantic Salmon Fry -->
